features.name: Alar Base Junction/Alar Crease - left
features.description: The junction between the left alar crease and the cheek.

features.name: Alar Base Junction/Alar Crease - right
features.description: The junction between the right alar crease and the cheek.

features.name: Alar Rim’s Highest Point - left
features.description: The highest point of the left alar rim.

features.name: Alar Rim’s Highest Point - right
features.description: The highest point of the right alar rim.

features.name: Alare/Alar Flare - left
features.description: The most lateral point on the left ala of the nose.

features.name: Alare/Alar Flare - right
features.description: The most lateral point on the right ala of the nose.

features.name: Columellar Break Point
features.description: The point in the columellar region of the nose where the tip of the nose stops curving and the columellar linear structure begins, in the midline.

features.name: Endocanthion/Medial Canthus - left
features.description: The inner corner of the left eye where the upper and lower eyelids meet.

features.name: Endocanthion/Medial Canthus - right
features.description: The inner corner of the right eye where the upper and lower eyelids meet.

features.name: Glabella
features.description: The most prominent point of the forehead in the midline between the eyebrows.

features.name: Labiale Superius
features.description: The midline point representing the mucocutaneous vermilion border of the upper lip

features.name: Maxilloanteriorale - left
features.description: The point where the left maxilloanterioral and nasoanterioral sutures meet

features.name: Maxilloanteriorale - right
features.description: The point where the right maxilloanterioral and nasoanterioral sutures meet

features.name: Maxillofrontale - left
features.description: The soft tissue point located at the left lateral margin of the base of the nasal root at the level of the endocanthion.

features.name: Maxillofrontale - right
features.description: The soft tissue point located at the right lateral margin of the base of the nasal root at the level of the endocanthion.

features.name: Menton/Gnathion
features.description: Lowest point on the soft tissue proﬁle of the chin in mid-sagittal plane.

features.name: Nasal Parenthesis - left
features.description: The summit of the left nasal parentheses/canthal-alar line.

features.name: Nasal Parenthesis - right
features.description: The summit of the right nasal parentheses/canthal-alar line.

features.name: Nasion/Radix
features.description: The midpoint of the nasofrontal suture line where the frontal bone and nasal bones join.

features.name: Pogonion
features.description: Most anterior point on the soft tissue profile of the chin in mid-sagittal plane.

features.name: Posterior Point of Nostril - left
features.description: The point where the left ala meets the nostril floor at a point corresponding to sbal.

features.name: Posterior Point of Nostril - right
features.description: The point where the right ala meets the nostril floor at a point corresponding to sbal.

features.name: Pronasale/Tip
features.description: The most protrusive point on the nasal tip in the midline.

features.name: Rhinion
features.description: Osseocartilaginous junction. A craniometric point corresponding to the lower end of the suture between the two nasal bones.

features.name: Subnasale - left
features.description: Indicates the midpoint of the left columella crest where the thickness of the columella (sn'-sn') is measured.

features.name: Subnasale - right
features.description: Indicates the midpoint of the right columella crest where the thickness of the columella (sn'-sn') is measured.

features.name: Subnasale
features.description: The midpoint of the columella base. The deepest point at the junction of the base of the columella and the upper lip in the midline. Located at the apex of the nasolabial angle in the midline, where the inferior border of the nasal septum meets the skin of the upper lip.

features.name: Supratip Break Point
features.description: The area just cephalad to the nasal tip at the caudal portion of the nasal dorsum.

features.name: Tip Defining Point - left
features.description: The nasal tip defining point (TDP) is the most anterior projection of the tip cartilages, usually corresponding to the apex of the lobular arch anatomically, and is typically identified externally where the light reflex is seen on the nasal tip.

features.name: Tip Defining Point - right
features.description: The nasal tip defining point (TDP) is the most anterior projection of the tip cartilages, usually corresponding to the apex of the lobular arch anatomically, and is typically identified externally where the light reflex is seen on the nasal tip.

features.name: Tragion - left
features.description: The notch on the upper margin of the left tragus. A bilateral landmark located within the small notch at the superior extent of the tragus (cartilaginous projection just anterior to the auditory meatus), where the cartilage meets the face.

features.name: Tragion - right
features.description: The notch on the upper margin of the right tragus. A bilateral landmark located within the small notch at the superior extent of the tragus (cartilaginous projection just anterior to the auditory meatus), where the cartilage meets the face.

features.name: Trichion
features.description: The point on the hairline in the midline of the forehead.

features.name: Vertex
features.description: The topmost point of the vault of the cranium.

measurements.name: Ala/Alar Length (left)
measurements.description: The distance from pronasale/tip (prn) to alar base junction/alar crease - left (ac_l)

measurements.name: Ala/Alar Length (right)
measurements.description: The distance from pronasale/tip (prn) to alar base junction/alar crease - right (ac_r)

measurements.name: Alar Base Width
measurements.description: The distance from alar base junction/alar crease - left (ac_l) to alar base junction/alar crease - right (ac_r)

measurements.name: Base Bony Width
measurements.description: The distance from nasal parenthesis - left (np_l) to nasal parenthesis - right (np_r)

measurements.name: Columella Length
measurements.description: The distance between subnasale (sn) and columella breakpoint (cb)

measurements.name: Columella Width
measurements.description: The distance from subnasale - left (sn_l) to subnasale - right (sn_r)

measurements.name: Infratip Lobule Length
measurements.description: The distance from pronasale/tip (prn) to columella break point (cb)

measurements.name: Interalar Distance
measurements.description: The distance from alare/alar flare - left (al_l) to alar/alar flare - right (al_r).

measurements.name: (Inner) Intercanthal Distance/Width
measurements.description: The distance from endocanthion/medial canthus - left (en_l) to endocanthion/medial canthus - right (en_r)

measurements.name: Mid-Facial Height
measurements.description: The distance between subnasale (sn) and glabella (g)

measurements.name: Nasal Bridge Length
measurements.description: The distance from pronasale/tip (prn) to nasion (n)

measurements.name: Nasal Root Width
measurements.description: Distance from maxillofrontale - left (mf_l) to maxillofrontale - right (mf_r)

measurements.name: Nasal Tip Projection
measurements.description: The distance from pronasale/Tip (prn) to subnasale (sn)

measurements.name: Nose Height
measurements.description: The distance from Subnasale (sn) to Nasion (n)

measurements.name: Premaxilla - left
measurements.description: The distance between subnasale (sn) and alar base junction/alar crease - left (ac_l)

measurements.name: Premaxilla - right
measurements.description: The distance between subnasale (sn) and alar base junction/alar crease - right (ac_r)

measurements.name: Supratip Lobule
measurements.description: The distance from pronasale/tip (prn) to supratip break point (s)

measurements.name: Tip/Lobule Width
measurements.description: The distance from tip defining point - left (td_l) to tip defining point - right (td_r)

measurements.name: Alar Base Width - Surface
measurements.description: The surface distance from alar base junction/alar crease - left (ac_l) to alar base junction/alar crease - right (ac_r)
measurements.references: Please check the corresponding 'not surface' measurement

measurements.name: Columella Length - Surface
measurements.description: The surface distance between subnasale (sn) and columella breakpoint (cb)
measurements.references: Please check the corresponding 'not surface' measurement

measurements.name: Columella Width - Surface
measurements.description: The surface distance from subnasale - left (sn_l) to subnasale - right (sn_r)
measurements.references: Please check the corresponding 'not surface' measurement

measurements.name: Interalar Distance - Surface
measurements.description: The surface distance from alare/alar flare - left (al_l) to alar/alar flare - right (al_r).
measurements.references: Please check the corresponding 'not surface' measurement

measurements.name: Nasal Bridge Length - Surface
measurements.description: The surface distance from pronasale/tip (prn) to nasion (n)
measurements.references: Please check the corresponding 'not surface' measurement

measurements.name: Nasal Tip Projection - Surface
measurements.description: The surface distance from pronasale/Tip (prn) to subnasale (sn)
measurements.references: Please check the corresponding 'not surface' measurement

measurements.name: Interalar Angle
measurements.description: The angle from alare/alar flare – right (al_r) to nasal tip/pronasale (prn) to alare/alar flare – left (al_l).

measurements.name: Nasal Tip Angle
measurements.description: The angle between nasion/radix (n) to pronasale/tip (prn) to subnasale (sn).

measurements.name: Nasofrontal Angle
measurements.description: The angle from glabella (g) to nasion/radix (n) to pronasale/tip (prn)

measurements.name: Nasolabial Angle I
measurements.description: The angle from pronasale/tip (prn) to subnasale (sn) to labiale superius (ls)

measurements.name: Nasal Tip Projection: Goode
measurements.description: The distance from pronasale (prn) to alar base junction/alar crease - right (ac_r) divided by the distance from nasion (n) to nasal tip/pronasale (prn).

measurements.name: Nasal Width-Length Ratio
measurements.description: The alar base width divided by the nasal bridge length.
